hawk
====

This is my toy project. I've always been interested in parsers, languages and
so on, so I decided to make an Awk clone. You can have a look at test/run
directory to see some examples of what is implemented in the language.

Examples
--------

    1. emulate wc.

        { chars += len($0) + 1; words += NF }
        END { printf "%7d %7d %7d\n", NR, words, chars }

    2. filter values of a list.

           92 ./value/undefined.go
          260 ./value/value.go
          140 ./value/array.go
          136 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/semantic.go
          319 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/expr.go
          339 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/lex.go
          211 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/syntax.go
           71 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/builtin.go
          277 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/stmt.go
         1214 ./compiler/internal/hawkc/hawk.go
           35 ./compiler/compiler.go
          332 ./scan/scan.go
           91 ./scan/scan_test.go
           82 ./main.go
          105 ./test/errcheck/short_test.go
           47 ./test/run/run_test.go

        $1 > 200

    3. summarise a shopping list.

        lunch	4.99
        lunch	3.99
        snack	1
        lunch	2.49
        snack	0.89
        coffee	2.49
        lunch	3.20

        { m[$1] += $2 }
        END {
            for k, v in m {
                print v, k
            } | "sort -n"
        }
